  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nFor #930, the first thing we can do is moving some basic utils to Py-EVM.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\nIn beacon_chain repo [beacon_chain/utils](https://github.com/ethereum/beacon_chain/tree/master/beacon_chain/utils), all pure functions:\r\n\r\n1. `bitfields.py` - the APIs for operating bitfield\r\n2. `bls.py` - the APIs of BLS signature (BN128 curve currently, will change to BLS12-381 curve in other PRs).\r\n3. `blake.py` - a wrapper of blake2b. The reason why we use `blake2b(x).digest()[:32]` instead of `blake2b(x, digest_size=32)` is because using default algorithm is easier to tinker and some libraries may not support digest sizes for generating 32 bytes output.\r\n\r\nAction: move these utils APIs to `eth/utils/`, and the tests.\r\n",
